In another suit Cantilupe resolutely braved the resentment of the great baron, whose support had given to Prince Edward the crowning victory of Evesham. Grilbert de Clare, Earl of Gloucester‚ had taken possession with his foresters of the episcopal Chase of Eastnor and Colwall above Ledbury‚ which had been given to the See by King Medruth with confirmation from Pope Innocent 11.;³ and this without protest apparently from John le Breton. His successor lost no time in insisting on his rights. The Earl was summoned to defend his trespass (Oct, 1275), but his great influence intimidated at first the local officers ; many adjournments were allowed, which delayed the issue for two years.
